{"履修期": "春学期", "主な教授言語": "英語", "授業目的": "Please refer to the English section.", "到達目標": "Please refer to the English section.", "特記事項": "", "関連科目": "", "授業の概要・背景": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 8pt;line-height:18.4px;font-size:12pt;font-family:Aptos,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:Times,serif;font-size:10pt;line-height:15.3333px;background-image:initial;background-position:initial;background-size:initial;background-repeat:initial;background-attachment:initial;background-origin:initial;background-clip:initial;\">Skills-based English(Reading)L1 </span><span lang=\"EN-US\" times=\"times\" new=\"new\" roman\",serif;\"=\"roman',serif;'\" style=\"font-size:10pt;line-height:15.3333px;font-family:;\">is a once-a-week course designed to help learners develop their reading skills. Students will read a variety of texts and complete various types of tasks including interpretation and discussion activities. Learners will develop reading speed, vocabulary, and reading skills to help improve their academic reading ability.</span></p>", "授業方法": "This class will be completed entirely in English and consist of lectures, seminars, discussions, presentations and pair and group work. Students will do both extensive reading (for enjoyment &amp; fluency) and intensive reading (for language development and knowledge building). Students will also take part in pair and group discussions related to text topics. Finally, learners will build vocabulary and develop reading skills which will be beneficial for further learning, improved language test scores, and future language use.Students will need a Gmail account to access Google Classroom. Most assignments and quizzes/short tests will be collected online. IMPORTANT: You must have space in your Google Drive. If your Google Drive is full (15GB) of photos, videos, or other documents, you will not be able to see class material or assignments.", "トピック": {"第1回": ["<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 8pt;line-height: